history.content: You should definitely take an upper division probability course, CS70 is not enough. I postponed CS189 by one semester to take EECS126 and I am so grateful I did. Because I took 126, I understand the motivations for each of the techniques we study, and the math is really quite beautiful. I don’t think 110 would be particularly helpful, EECS127 is definitely the next best to take after 126.

children.subject: I also wouldn't take 189 over the summer. It's an extremely dense course in terms of things to learn, and to learn that in 8 weeks wouldn't be very helpful. Also, this is the first time 189 is being offered in the summer, so there's no way to gauge what it'll be like (it WILL be hell though).
I am also currently taking 189 but I did find 110 to be pretty useful! But IMO 127 will be much more useful because 189 is basically just 127 with a bunch of probability thrown in.
How did you find it useful? I'm seriously considering taking Math 110 before EECS 127 to fully master Linear Algebra but I've taken 2 Linear Algebra classes already (Math 54 and Stat 89A)
I'm currently taking 189 so take my advice with a grain of salt, but I took math 110 the semester before and it hasn't been very useful.

Oh also, I'd strongly recommend not taking it over summer - as already mentioned, 189 is a very dense course already, so they'll either kill you trying to fit everything into a dinner session, or (more likely) so various parts

I took CS189 last semester with Professor Sahai, and got an A+. My background was the normal EECS background (61 series, 70, 16a/b). No upper div math/stats, no 126/127. 

I did have to put 15+ hours a week into the class, especially for the more math/stats-heavy sections. In terms of ideal prerequisites, from what I've heard/seen, I think it's 126 > 127 > 110.

history.content:
I'm considering taking CS189 either in the Fall or over the Summer but not sure which one to do since I see positives and negatives to both. The way I see it, I have three options since I am graduating after the Fall semester. Wondering which option is best.

1) Take 189 in the Fall along with 3 other technicals I have to take. That would allow me to take Math 110, Stat 134, and (maybe) Stat 135 over the summer to prepare me. My only concern is that these classes won't actually help me much in 189 and that I'll be wasting my money, time, and forgoing a possible internship. Has anyone taken 110, 134, or 135 before 189 (without CS126 or CS127)? If so, how helpful were those classes?

2) Take 189 over the summer as my only class and dedicate all my time to understanding the material, even if my background is less than ideal.

3) Take an internship over the summer and take 189 in the fall without taking any classes over the summer.

For reference, I am taking CS70 this semester. I have taken Math 53, Math 54, and am currently taking Math 126 (Partial Differential Equations; not necessarily applicable to 189 but may help in terms of overall mathematical maturity).

Thanks in advance for the advice!
history.subject: Preparing for CS189
